==================================================
FINAL DIAGNOSTICS
==================================================

Interpretation guide:

1. If:
   R_dataset ~= R_reconstructed

   then quaternion conversion is CORRECT.

2. If transpose suddenly produces intuitive angles:
   your dataset uses opposite transform direction.

3. If axis fix suddenly produces intuitive angles:
   Blender/OpenCV frame mismatch.

4. If BOTH fixes are needed:
   dataset stores:
       object->camera
   while your math assumes:
       camera->object

5. If ALL reconstructed matrices match originals,
   but Euler angles still look wrong:

   Then the issue is ONLY Euler convention ambiguity,
   not quaternion or matrix conversion.

